Nippon Steel Corp &lt;NSTC.TOK> said it willcut its capital spending by 36.4 pct to 105 billion yen in theyear starting April 1 from a year earlier due to thepostponement of furnace improvements.    &lt;Nisshin Steel Co Ltd> said it will spend 10.7 billion yenin 1987/88 for rationalisation and facility improvements, downfrom 32.1 billion a year earlier, after completion of largeconstruction projects in 1986/87.    But capital spending by Nippon Kokan K.K. &lt;NKKT.TOK> toimprove and increase its production facilities will rise to94.90 billion yen from 64 billion, the company said. REUTER&#3;